  "prompt": "When were cotton fibres first used?",
  "response": "Cotton fibers have been used for thousands of years. The earliest evidence of cotton usage dates back to around 5000 BCE in the Indus Valley, where archaeologists found cotton textiles. Additionally, cotton was also being spun and woven in parts of South America, particularly ancient Peru, around the same time. The cultivation and use of cotton spread over the centuries, becoming a significant crop and textile in various cultures around the world.",
